    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nGlobal value of `ignorecase` is changed when editing `ada` files.\r\nI assume the same is the case for `hamster` files (based on a grep of the neovim runtime).\r\n\r\nI believe the reason is that the `ignorecase` option is global, but `ada.vim` attempts to set it locally (inadvertantly setting it globally).\r\n```\r\nneovim [16:18:40] % grep -A8 \"\\*'ignorecase'\" runtime/doc/options.txt\r\n                        *'ignorecase'* *'ic'* *'noignorecase'* *'noic'*\r\n'ignorecase' 'ic'       boolean (default off)\r\n                        global\r\n        Ignore case in search patterns, |cmdline-completion|, when\r\n        searching in the tags file, and |expr-==|.\r\n        Also see 'smartcase' and 'tagcase'.\r\n        Can be overruled by using \"\\c\" or \"\\C\" in the pattern, see\r\n        |/ignorecase|.\r\n\r\nneovim [16:18:46] %\r\nneovim [16:18:57] % git grep -n 'setlocal.*ignorecase'\r\nruntime/ftplugin/ada.vim:52:setlocal ignorecase\r\nruntime/ftplugin/hamster.vim:60:setlocal ignorecase\r\nruntime/syntax/baan.vim:15:\"setlocal ignorecase         \"This is not a local yet ;-(\r\nneovim [16:19:00] %\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:setglobal ignorecase?\r\n:edit test.ada\r\n:setglobal ignorecase?\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nGlobal value of `ignorecase` should not have changed.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.0-dev-422+g3c803483a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes.  vim 9.1 with patches 1.16, 647, 678\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nXterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source.",
